Description: Quigler is an app that provides possible transparency and accountability from real estate agents for buyers, sellers, and tenants.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Quigler is a SaaS transaction and compliance manager for real estate agents and consumers. It is a tool for agents to provide consumers transparency and accountability for the largest financial transaction of consumers' lives: the purchase or sale of a home. Quigler takes what federal and state law and the NAR Code of Ethics requires agents (and consumers) to do in a transaction, organizes those "actions" into a sequential  checklist of Steps that mirror the flow of the transaction, with simple "yes" or "no" Actions under each Step, i.e. did you do this? did you fill out this form?   Consumers can follow the transaction 24/7, always know where they and their agent are in the transaction, what is required, when it must done, the penalty for non-compliance and the forms required to accomplish the task. Its mission is to help agents automate an excellent experience for buyer and seller clients. Quigler is free to consumers. Agents pay a yearly fee to use it as a transaction management application with their consumer clients.  By providing consumers with much wanted transparency, communication and accountability, it helps agents build a consumer's trust that can serve agents as a lifelong business generation tool. Because Quigler is a compliance tool, lowering the risk of complaints and/or litigation, Brokers can earn risk reduction credits from their Errors & Omissions insurers and reduce their insurance premiums. Quigler was founded in 2015

Description: TI International is a provider of enterprise data integration solutions.
Full Description: ETI International Inc., also known as Evolutionary Technologies International, Inc., provides enterprise data integration solutions. Its products include ETI Solution, a data integration platform that enables data integration from Java/XML to legacy COBOL, proprietary, or multibyte data; and Built-to-Order Integration that provides built-to-order connectors, which integrate mainframe, legacy, and proprietary applications with current business intelligence, data warehousing, and SOA-based infrastructures. The company also provides data quality solutions, such as Data Profiler that includes counts, advanced statistics, pattern recognition, inconsistency identification, anomalies, possible key values, and data relationships for analysis to discover the content, structure, and quality of data sources before the start of information technology project; Data Monitor that helps to remove the hidden business costs attributable to bad data by examining the data quality of vital business processes, applications, and information technology projects; and Data Cleanser that enables to design, manage, and deploy cleansing processes, which run in line with production systems or offline for batch-based projects. Further, the company provides implementation and consulting, education and training, and customer support services. But our pledge to personal service and representation doesn't just come to an end with a signed check. Many big law firms like to advertise big cases and verdicts because these cases mean they’ve been paid a large sum of money. But how does a dubious plan like this help you? A huge settlement may look great on paper, but after everyone has taken his or her cut then you’re probably not left with anywhere near as much as what you wanted or felt you deserved. The good thing about our firm is that we don’t work just for the money – we work for you! What matters most to us is not the settlement number – but instead it’s about maximizing the amount you can take home and keep for yourself and family. Even after you receive your settlement or judgment, we continue to work for you by helping you get the maximum value out of your lawsuit. We’re able to negotiate with doctors, insurance companies, even Medicare and/or Medicaid to help you save a larger amount of your settlement or judgment. Then we help advice you on how to protect that money so it will be long-term and when you need it most. ClearSight Networks, Inc. provides network monitoring and analysis solutions for real-time application troubleshooting. It offers
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: ClearSight Networks, Inc. provides network monitoring and analysis solutions for real-time application troubleshooting. It offers ClearSight Cronos, a network management solution that characterizes and measures latency and packet loss information of trading networks over a period of time; ClearSight Apex, a network analysis engine for problem diagnosis and resolution in enterprise networks; and ClearSight Analyzer, an application and network monitoring and troubleshooting solution. The company also provides ClearSight Network Time Machine, a data capture and analysis system that is used to manage and diagnose problems affecting Ethernet-based enterprise networks. In addition, it offers a network health check program that allows users to monitor the performance of their enterprise networks; and courses on various subjects covering protocol architecture, low-level protocol debug and analysis, and ClearSight product training and certification preparation to technology professionals. The company's solutions are used in IPTV analysis, VoIP analysis, data mining, long-term network traffic capture, and low latency measurements applications. It was formerly known as AppDancer Networks, Inc. and changed its name to ClearSight Networks, Inc. in 2003. The company was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Fremont, California with additional offices in the United States. As of December 29, 2009, ClearSight Networks, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Fluke Networks, Inc.

Full Description: Qumranet, Inc., an enterprise software company, provides virtual computing solutions. The company offers Solid ICE, an integrated desktop virtualization product. Its Solid ICE components comprise Virtual Desktop Server that runs the users Windows virtual desktop; Virtual Desktop Controller, which manages a virtual desktop environment; and Simple Protocol for Independent Computing Environments (SPICE) that is a remote connection protocol for virtual environments. The company's solutions enable enterprises to host desktops in Kernel-based virtual machines on servers in the corporate data center, and allow users to connect to them through a remote protocol called SPICE. Qumranet, Inc., formerly known as Comanet, was founded in 2005 and is based in Sunnyvale, California. The company has additional offices in Raanana and Netanya, Israel; and Sunnyvale, California.
